On the morning of August 12, the State Council Information Office held a press conference on the performance of the national economy in July 2016.
Sheng Laiyun, spokesperson of the National Bureau of Statistics and director of the National Economic Comprehensive Statistics Department, said that in July, the growth rate of some indicators of the national economy slowed down, but it was still operating within a reasonable range.
Data released by the National Bureau of Statistics show that fixed asset investment growth, total imports and other data fell back in July.
Sheng Laiyun said that regarding the performance of the national economy in July, I would like to borrow a sentence once said by the Prime Minister, &quot;There are fluctuations in the situation, but the trend is still improving.&quot; This can better summarize the characteristics of the economic performance in July.
He explained that &quot;tangible fluctuations&quot; meant that the growth rate of some economic indicators did drop in July.
Because the domestic and foreign economies were still undergoing deep adjustments in July, the international situation was complex and changeable, and the recovery of the world economy was less than expected, so export pressure was still relatively high.
Judging from the domestic situation, the entire economy is still in a critical stage of adjustment. The pain of adjustment is being released. The economy is facing considerable downward pressure, so some indicators have fluctuated.
Sheng Laiyun pointed out that there was another special situation in July. Floods were relatively serious, and high temperatures and hot weather had some impact on production and operations in some areas.
According to the latest information released by the Ministry of Civil Affairs, more than 60 million people across the country were affected by the disaster, with direct economic losses exceeding 200 billion yuan.
Judging from industry, investment, and transportation-related indicators, these regions have been affected to varying degrees.
The growth rate of cargo turnover in July dropped 3.6 percentage points from the previous month. Floods have had a certain impact on traffic in these areas.
Judging from these factors, it is normal and expected for some indicators to fluctuate in July.
He said that &quot;the trend is still improving&quot; means that although the economic growth rate has slowed down, the economic operation is generally stable, and the general trend of steady progress and steady improvement has not changed.
The CPI rose by 1.8% in July and 0.2% month-on-month; from January to July, the CPI rose by 2.1%, so the price situation is generally stable.
According to the statistics of high temperature weather in various districts and counties on the Chongqing Meteorological Bureau portal website, except for Youyang, the rest of the city can receive varying degrees of high temperature subsidies.
At present, at least 28 provinces across the country have clarified the subsidy payment standards, but the standards for each province and city are different. Chongqing receives high temperature subsidies in the form of high temperature working day allowances.
If the temperature is above 35℃ and below 37℃, the payment will be at a standard of no less than 10 yuan per person per day; if the temperature is above 37℃, the payment will be at a standard of no less than 15 yuan per person per day.
Workers working in high temperatures above 40°C can receive up to 20 yuan/day in monthly allowances (except for workers who already enjoy high-temperature job allowances in accordance with the law).
According to this standard, Kaizhou, which had the most hot weather days last month, can receive 330 yuan, and Chengkou, which has the fewest days, can receive 80 yuan. However, since the highest temperature in Youyang did not meet the high temperature standard, there is no high temperature allowance.
In the past, many units would use refreshing drinks to offset the high temperature allowance. The Municipal Work Safety Bureau said that this behavior was not in line with current measures.
If work is stopped or working hours are shortened due to hot weather, the employer shall not deduct or reduce workers&#39; wages.
The Municipal Human Resources and Social Security Bureau stated that employees who encounter high temperatures but do not receive high temperature allowances can fight for their legitimate rights and interests through the labor dispute mediation agency where the company is located, or call 12333 to complain.
If the employing unit refuses to pay the high temperature allowance, the worker may complain to the human resources and social security department at or above the county level where the employer is located.
At the same time, since the high temperature allowance is part of the salary, not a benefit, it must be included in the total salary and personal tax deducted.
Therefore, high temperature allowance is not within the scope of the minimum wage and must be paid in cash and cannot be replaced by physical items such as drinks.
The newly built Urumqi Station is located in the high-speed railway area of Urumqi, with a total construction area of approximately 100,000 square meters.
