While a stable ionosphere with lots of free electrons could help people listen to a college radio station at the edge of its range, that might not be what the Air Force is interested in.
An electron-filled ionosphere means radios used by the military have a greater range, and it may provide some protection for Global Positioning System (GPS) signals from solar storms.
The ultimate goal may be to create an on-demand fleet of CubeSats that can bolster the ionosphere when needed.
