Industry data shows that the total coal production capacity in 2015 was close to 6 billion tons, and the country&#39;s coal production capacity was 1.8 billion tons.
In the past ten years, the State Council has issued five notices to eliminate excess and backward production capacity.
Although the coal industry was not targeted in the first four times, the target industries were directly related to the coal industry.
From November last year to January this year, the price of 5,500 kcal thermal coal in Qinhuangdao hovered at a low of 370 yuan/ton for a long time, and 90% of coal companies fell into losses.
Since February, coal prices have gradually recovered. Recently, Qinhuangdao thermal coal prices have risen for four consecutive weeks, rising to a 16-month high, once climbing to 436 yuan per ton, nearly 70 yuan higher than at the beginning of the year.
As prices rebound, concerns arise from all walks of life: Will a group of small coal mines resume work and production?
In this regard, Kuang Xianming, director of the Economics Institute of the China (Hainan) Reform and Development Research Institute, conducted an analysis and interpretation.
Kuang Xianming: Overcapacity reduction has attracted great attention from all parties. The report card on overcapacity reduction in the coal industry announced today has indeed made everyone worried.
These three superficial factors still reflect the reason why the transformation of our growth mode has lagged behind in the past, that is, the government-led growth mode has not yet undergone a fundamental transformation.
Second, this is also directly related to the advancement of local governments. In the process of overcapacity reduction, funds and corresponding supporting measures must be in place. From this aspect, the differences between different regions are indeed relatively large.
Third, if some provinces that are currently progressing slowly have to catch up in the second half of the year, they may face greater risks.
In this case, relying on central government subsidies and subsidies to promote the process of overcapacity reduction may have certain negative effects.
First of all, cutting overcapacity is not simply about total volume control.
Our purpose is to eliminate backward production capacity, promote structural optimization, and reconstruct the entire coal industry&#39;s new business format.
In the process of deploying overcapacity reduction, local governments must combine overcapacity reduction with the transformation and upgrading of the coal industry and vigorously develop related service industries.
Second, if we want to complete this year&#39;s overcapacity reduction task within this year, we still need to give full play to the power of administrative supervision and administrative supervision.
Finally, we must strengthen the protective role of social security.
Because the market is directly related to employment issues, we must strengthen employment skills training for employees and workers.
