Snapchat&#39;s &#39;anime&#39; effect accused of mocking Asians
Snapchat said the filter was inspired by anime, but some observers thought it had racial undertones.
Snapchat’s 150 million daily users can use its filter tool to alter reality and turn portraits into comical moments.
You can transform yourself into a pineapple, a dog or a character from a Roy Lichtenstein painting.
