Implementing trade protection measures will not help fundamentally solve the development problems of the global steel industry. On the contrary, it will only cause further impact on the international trade order.
When talking about debt, the person in charge emphasized that resolving the debt problem is an important issue that needs to be properly handled in the process of resolving excess production capacity.
Due to the large scale of assets of steel companies and their wide coverage, some companies have complex debt relationships. If they are not handled properly, they may lead to regional risks.
According to the person in charge, in recent years, as the downward pressure on the economy has increased, total social demand has gradually weakened, the capacity utilization rate of some industries has declined, and the production and operation difficulties of enterprises have increased.
