The existence of such enterprises distorts market signals, reduces the efficiency of factor resource utilization, increases social management costs, and hinders the establishment of a fair competitive market environment.
The main reasons for the losses are the same as the difficulties faced by the global steel industry - weak market demand and low capacity utilization.
Our country mainly adopts market mechanisms, economic means and legal measures. The government mainly does a good job in protecting employees and social stability, and ensuring a fair and just market order.
The person in charge emphasized that in the next step, we must unswervingly continue to work on reducing overcapacity and ensure that the target task of reducing crude steel production capacity by 100 million to 150 million tons in five years is completed.
